            <p>Ooty is a town and hill station in the Indian state of Tamil Nadu. <br>The name "Ooty" is short for Ootacamund (officially Udhagamandalam).<br> Ooty is located in the Nilgiris district, or Blue Mountains, <br>a mountain district. Ooty stands at about 7,500 feet above sea level.</p>
            <p>Peppered with coffee and tea plantations, forests of eucalyptus, <br>conifers and pines, and a thick cover of shola trees, Ootacamund is <br>the perfect getaway for nature lovers. Such is the renown of its <br>beauty that it is popularly referred to as the 'Queen of Hill Stations' <br>and the 'Switzerland of India'.</p>
